{{Sagittarius}}
Sagittarius is the 1st month of the [[Gaian calendar]]. It contains 28 days (4 weeks) and corresponds to ISO weeks 1–4.
== Overview == ===Etymology=== English ''Sagittarius'' "the Archer" (Latin < ''sagitta'' "arrow"). Japanese: {{ill|射手座|ja|Ite-za}} “archer-constellation.” ===Gaiad themes=== Covers Weeks 1–4 (Days [[Sagittarius 1]]–[[Sagittarius 28]]): **Creation of the universe**, **Migration to Earth**, **Eukaryogenesis**, **Boring Billion**—Aster spins the cosmos, early life takes shape, and deep-time diversification begins.
All precambrian ===EVENTS=== * [[Sagittarius 1]] — New Years (Aster Day) * [[Sagittarius 8]] — Coming of Age Day
==REFERENCES== [[Category:Gaian calendar months]]
