{{Aquarius}}
Aquarius is the 3rd month of the [[Gaian calendar]]. It contains 28 days (4 weeks) and corresponds to ISO weeks 9–12.
== Overview == Life on Land develops ===Etymology=== English ''Aquarius'' "water-bearer" (Latin). Japanese: {{ill|水瓶座|ja|Mizugame-za}} “water-jar constellation.” ===Gaiad themes=== Weeks 9–12 (Days [[Aquarius 1]]–[[Aquarius 28]]): late **Devonian** transitions, early **Carboniferous** dawn, land vertebrate adaptations, and continental eco-shifts. ===EVENTS=== * [[Aquarius 7]] — [[:Category:Days_that_Hinamatsuri_falls_on|Hinamatsuri]] * [[Aquarius 21]] — [[:Category:Days_that_Kōrei-sai_(皇霊祭)_falls_on|Kōrei-sai]], Ides of March, St Patricks day * [[Aquarius 28]] — Easter Sunday
