{{Ophiuchus}}
Ophiuchus is the 13th month of the [[Gaian calendar]]. It contains 28 days (4 weeks) and corresponds to ISO weeks 49–52.
== Overview == ===Etymology=== English ''Ophiuchus'' "the Serpent-Bearer" (Greek ''ophis'' serpent + ''ekhein'' to hold). Japanese: {{ill|蛇遣座|ja|Hebitsukai-za}} “snake-handler constellation.” '''Note:''' In popular astrology Ophiuchus is sometimes called a "13th sign." In the Gaian system it is a full month (Days [[Ophiuchus 1]]–[[Ophiuchus 28]]) preceding the intercalary **Horus** month. ===Gaiad themes=== Weeks 49–52 (Days [[Ophiuchus 1]]–[[Ophiuchus 28]]): ===EVENTS=== * [[Ophiuchus 21]] — [[:Category:Days_that_Christmas_Day_falls_on|Christmas Day]] / Dongzhi Festival
==REFERENCES== [[Category:Gaian calendar months]]
